Pakistan Banks to Close on First Ramadan; New Business Timings

-- B y   F a r h a n   S h a r i f
-- 
2011-08-01T08:42:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/pakistan-banks-to-close-on-first-ramadan-new-business-timings.html
State Bank of Pakistan , the central
bank, and all commercial lenders will be closed on the first day
of Ramadan, the start of the Muslim holy month of fasting, to
deduct Zakaat, a 2.5 percent tax on savings in banks.  They will open on the next working day, according to an e-
mailed statement by the Karachi-based central bank. Ramadan is
expected to begin either tomorrow or on Aug. 3 in  Pakistan .  Banks will open at 8:30 a.m. local time and close at 1:00
p.m. from Monday to Thursday and on Saturday during Ramadan. On
Friday, banks will open at 8:30 a.m. local time and close at
12:00 p.m.  Pakistanâ€™s stock exchange will start trading at 9:15 a.m.
local time and end at 2:00 p.m. from Monday to Thursday,
according to a statement on the Web site of the  Karachi Stock
Exchange . On Fridays, share trading will take place between 9:15
a.m. and 12:30 p.m.  To contact the reporter on this story:
